<span class="comment"><font color=#000000>Yes I did. It was very hard work. I combed through hundreds of adds, sent custom replies to several dozen of the most promising and made it clear that I was offering high quality, with the unstated caveat that I was not offering the lowest price. I replied only to adds local to Boston (where I live) and said that I would be happy to come to their location at their convenience. When I did in person interview I dressed very well, and read up extensively on their companies beforehand. I did not even entertain anyone that seemed like a cheapskate or wanted to offer equity.</font></span><p><font size=1><u><a href="reply?id=3548898&whence=%69%74%65%6d%3f%69%64%3d%33%35%33%33%32%35%36">reply</a></u></font></td></tr></table></td></tr><tr><td><table border=0><tr><td><img src="http://ycombinator.com/images/s.gif" height=1 width=120></td><td valign=top><center><a id=up_3533937 href="vote?for=3533937&dir=up&whence=%74%68%72%65%61%64%73%3f%69%64%3d%70%61%74%69%6f%31%31"><img src="http://ycombinator.com/images/grayarrow.gif" border=0 vspace=3 hspace=2></a><span id=down_3533937></span></center></td><td class="default"><div style="margin-top:2px; margin-bottom:-10px; "><span class="comhead"><a href="user?id=chc">chc</a> 4 days ago  | <a href="item?id=3533937">link</a></span></div><br>
